228 // ******************************************************************************************
229 // start thread generating the collision table
230 // ******************************************************************************************
231 void DefaultCollisionsWidget::startGeneratingCollisionTable()
232 {
233  // Disable controls on form
234  disableControls(true);
235  btn_revert_->setEnabled(true); // allow to interrupt and revert
236 
237  // create a MonitorThread running generateCollisionTable() in a worker thread and monitoring the progress
238  worker_ = new MonitorThread(boost::bind(&DefaultCollisionsWidget::generateCollisionTable, this, _1), progress_bar_);
239  connect(worker_, SIGNAL(finished()), this, SLOT(finishGeneratingCollisionTable()));
240  worker_->start(); // start after having finished() signal connected
241 }
242 
243 // ******************************************************************************************
244 // cleanup after worker_ thread has finished
245 // ******************************************************************************************
246 void DefaultCollisionsWidget::finishGeneratingCollisionTable()
247 {
248  if (worker_->canceled())
249  return;
250 
251  // Load the results into the GUI
252  loadCollisionTable();
253 
254  // Hide the progress bar
255  disableControls(false); // enable everything else
256 
257  config_data_->changes |= MoveItConfigData::COLLISIONS;
258  worker_->deleteLater();
259  worker_ = nullptr;
260 }
261 
262 // ******************************************************************************************
263 // The worker function to compute the collision matrix
264 // ******************************************************************************************
265 void DefaultCollisionsWidget::generateCollisionTable(unsigned int* collision_progress)
266 {
267  unsigned int num_trials = density_slider_->value() * 1000 + 1000; // scale to trials amount
268  double min_frac = (double)fraction_spinbox_->value() / 100.0;
269 
270  const bool verbose = true; // Output benchmarking and statistics
271  const bool include_never_colliding = true;
272 
273  // clear previously loaded collision matrix entries
274  config_data_->getPlanningScene()->getAllowedCollisionMatrixNonConst().clear();
275 
276  // Find the default collision matrix - all links that are allowed to collide
277  link_pairs_ = moveit_setup_assistant::computeDefaultCollisions(
278  config_data_->getPlanningScene(), collision_progress, include_never_colliding, num_trials, min_frac, verbose);
279 
280  // End the progress bar loop
281  *collision_progress = 100;
282 
283  ROS_INFO_STREAM("Thread complete " << link_pairs_.size());
284 }
285 
286 // ******************************************************************************************
287 // Displays data in the link_pairs_ data structure into a QtTableWidget
288 // ******************************************************************************************
289 void DefaultCollisionsWidget::loadCollisionTable()
290 {
291  CollisionMatrixModel* matrix_model = new CollisionMatrixModel(
292  link_pairs_, config_data_->getPlanningScene()->getRobotModel()->getLinkModelNamesWithCollisionGeometry());
293  QAbstractItemModel* model;
294 
295  if (view_mode_buttons_->checkedId() == MATRIX_MODE)
296  {
297  model = matrix_model;
298  }
299  else
300  {
301  CollisionLinearModel* linear_model = new CollisionLinearModel(matrix_model);
302  SortFilterProxyModel* sorted_model = new SortFilterProxyModel();
303  model = sorted_model;
304  sorted_model->setSourceModel(linear_model);
305  // ensure deletion of underlying models with model
306  linear_model->setParent(sorted_model);
307  matrix_model->setParent(linear_model);
308  }
309  connect(link_name_filter_, SIGNAL(textChanged(QString)), model, SLOT(setFilterRegExp(QString)));
310  QMetaObject::invokeMethod(model, "setFilterRegExp", Q_ARG(QString, link_name_filter_->text()));
311 
312  collision_table_->setModel(model);
313  // delete old and remember new model
314  delete model_;
315  model_ = model;
316 
317  // delete old and fetch new selection model
318  delete selection_model_;
319  selection_model_ = collision_table_->selectionModel();
320 
321  QHeaderView *horizontal_header, *vertical_header;
322 
323  // activate some model-specific settings
324  if (view_mode_buttons_->checkedId() == MATRIX_MODE)
325  {
326  connect(selection_model_, SIGNAL(currentChanged(QModelIndex, QModelIndex)), this,
327  SLOT(previewSelectedMatrix(QModelIndex)));
328 
329  collision_table_->setSelectionBehavior(QAbstractItemView::SelectItems);
330  collision_table_->setSelectionMode(QAbstractItemView::ExtendedSelection);
331 
332  collision_table_->setHorizontalHeader(horizontal_header = new RotatedHeaderView(Qt::Horizontal, this));
333  collision_table_->setVerticalHeader(vertical_header = new RotatedHeaderView(Qt::Vertical, this));
334  collision_table_->setSortingEnabled(false);
335 
336  collision_checkbox_->hide();
337  horizontal_header->setVisible(true);
338  vertical_header->setVisible(true);
339 
340  horizontal_header->setContextMenuPolicy(Qt::CustomContextMenu);
341  connect(horizontal_header, SIGNAL(customContextMenuRequested(QPoint)), this, SLOT(showHeaderContextMenu(QPoint)));
342  vertical_header->setContextMenuPolicy(Qt::CustomContextMenu);
343  connect(vertical_header, SIGNAL(customContextMenuRequested(QPoint)), this, SLOT(showHeaderContextMenu(QPoint)));
344  }
345  else
346  {
347  connect(selection_model_, SIGNAL(currentChanged(QModelIndex, QModelIndex)), this,
348  SLOT(previewSelectedLinear(QModelIndex)));
349 
350  collision_table_->setSelectionBehavior(QAbstractItemView::SelectRows);
351  collision_table_->setSelectionMode(QAbstractItemView::ExtendedSelection);
352 
353  collision_table_->setHorizontalHeader(horizontal_header = new QHeaderView(Qt::Horizontal, this));
354  collision_table_->setVerticalHeader(vertical_header = new QHeaderView(Qt::Vertical, this));
355  collision_table_->sortByColumn(0, Qt::AscendingOrder);
356  collision_table_->setSortingEnabled(true);
357 
358  collision_checkbox_->show();
359  horizontal_header->setVisible(true);
360  vertical_header->setVisible(true);
361 
362  vertical_header->setContextMenuPolicy(Qt::CustomContextMenu);
363  connect(vertical_header, SIGNAL(customContextMenuRequested(QPoint)), this, SLOT(showHeaderContextMenu(QPoint)));
364 
365 #if (QT_VERSION >= QT_VERSION_CHECK(5, 0, 0))
366  horizontal_header->setSectionsClickable(true);
367  vertical_header->setSectionsClickable(true);
368 #else
369  horizontal_header->setClickable(true);
370  vertical_header->setClickable(true);
371 #endif
372  }
373 
374 // notice changes to the model
375 #if (QT_VERSION >= QT_VERSION_CHECK(5, 0, 0))
376  connect(model_, SIGNAL(dataChanged(QModelIndex, QModelIndex, QVector<int>)), this,
377  SLOT(collisionsChanged(QModelIndex)));
378 #else
379  connect(model_, SIGNAL(dataChanged(QModelIndex, QModelIndex)), this, SLOT(collisionsChanged(QModelIndex)));
380 #endif
381 }
382 
383 void DefaultCollisionsWidget::collisionsChanged(const QModelIndex& index)
384 {
385  btn_revert_->setEnabled(true); // enable revert button
386 
387  if (!index.isValid())
388  return;
389  // Hm. For some reason, QTableView doesn't change selection if we click a checkbox
390  bool linear_mode = (view_mode_buttons_->checkedId() == LINEAR_MODE);
391  const QItemSelection& selection = selection_model_->selection();
392  if ((linear_mode && !selection.contains(index)) || // in linear mode: index not in selection
393  (!linear_mode && !(selection.contains(index) || // in matrix mode: index or symmetric index not in selection
394  selection.contains(model_->index(index.column(), index.row())))))
395  {
396  QItemSelectionModel::SelectionFlags flags = QItemSelectionModel::Select | QItemSelectionModel::Current;
397  if (linear_mode)
398  flags |= QItemSelectionModel::Rows;
399  selection_model_->setCurrentIndex(index, flags);
400  }
401 }

403 void DefaultCollisionsWidget::showHeaderContextMenu(const QPoint& p)
404 {
405  // This method might be triggered from either of the headers
406  QPoint global;
407  if (sender() == collision_table_->verticalHeader())
408  {
409  clicked_section_ = collision_table_->verticalHeader()->logicalIndexAt(p);
410  clicked_headers_ = Qt::Vertical;
411  global = collision_table_->verticalHeader()->mapToGlobal(p);
412  }
413  else if (sender() == collision_table_->horizontalHeader())
414  {
415  clicked_section_ = collision_table_->horizontalHeader()->logicalIndexAt(p);
416  clicked_headers_ = Qt::Horizontal;
417  global = collision_table_->horizontalHeader()->mapToGlobal(p);
418  }
419  else
420  {
421  clicked_section_ = -1;
422  clicked_headers_ = Qt::Horizontal | Qt::Vertical;
423  }
424 
425  QMenu menu;
426  if (clicked_section_ < 0)
427  menu.addAction(header_actions_.at(0)); // only 'show' action
428  else
429  menu.addActions(header_actions_);
430  menu.exec(global);
431 
432  clicked_headers_ = {};
433  clicked_section_ = -1;
434 }

436 void DefaultCollisionsWidget::hideSections()
437 {
438  QList<int> list;
439  QHeaderView* header = nullptr;
440  if (clicked_headers_ == Qt::Horizontal)
441  {
442  for (const QModelIndex& index : selection_model_->selectedColumns())
443  list << index.column();
444  header = collision_table_->horizontalHeader();
445  }
446  else if (clicked_headers_ == Qt::Vertical)
447  {
448  for (const QModelIndex& index : selection_model_->selectedRows())
449  list << index.row();
450  header = collision_table_->verticalHeader();
451  }
452 
453  // if somewhere else than the selection was clicked, hide only this row/column
454  if (!list.contains(clicked_section_))
455  {
456  list.clear();
457  list << clicked_section_;
458  }
459 
460  for (auto index : list)
461  header->setSectionHidden(index, true);
462 }
463 
464 void DefaultCollisionsWidget::hideOtherSections()
465 {
466  QList<int> list;
467  QHeaderView* header = nullptr;
468  if (clicked_headers_ == Qt::Horizontal)
469  {
470  header = collision_table_->horizontalHeader();
471  for (const QModelIndex& index : selection_model_->selectedColumns())
472  if (!header->isSectionHidden(index.column()))
473  list << index.column();
474  }
475  else if (clicked_headers_ == Qt::Vertical)
476  {
477  header = collision_table_->verticalHeader();
478  for (const QModelIndex& index : selection_model_->selectedRows())
479  if (!header->isSectionHidden(index.row()))
480  list << index.row();
481  }
482 
483  // if somewhere else than the selection was clicked, hide only this row/column
484  if (!list.contains(clicked_section_))
485  {
486  list.clear();
487  list << clicked_section_;
488  }
489 
490  // first hide all sections
491  for (std::size_t index = 0, end = header->count(); index != end; ++index)
492  header->setSectionHidden(index, true);
493 
494  // and subsequently show selected ones
495  for (auto index : list)
496  header->setSectionHidden(index, false);
497 }

499 void DefaultCollisionsWidget::showSections()
500 {
501  QList<int> list;
502  if (clicked_section_ < 0) // show all
503  {
504  if (clicked_headers_.testFlag(Qt::Horizontal))
505  {
506  // show all columns
507  list.clear();
508  list << 0 << model_->columnCount() - 1;
509  showSections(collision_table_->horizontalHeader(), list);
510  }
511 
512  if (clicked_headers_.testFlag(Qt::Vertical)) // show all rows
513  {
514  list.clear();
515  list << 0 << model_->rowCount() - 1;
516  showSections(collision_table_->verticalHeader(), list);
517  }
518  return;
519  }
520 
521  QHeaderView* header = nullptr;
522  if (clicked_headers_ == Qt::Horizontal)
523  {
524  for (const QModelIndex& index : selection_model_->selectedColumns())
525  list << index.column();
526  header = collision_table_->horizontalHeader();
527  }
528  else if (clicked_headers_ == Qt::Vertical)
529  {
530  for (const QModelIndex& index : selection_model_->selectedRows())
531  list << index.row();
532  header = collision_table_->verticalHeader();
533  }
534 
535  // if somewhere else than the selection was clicked, hide only this row/column
536  if (!list.contains(clicked_section_))
537  {
538  list.clear();
539  list << clicked_section_;
540  }
541  showSections(header, list);
542 }
543 void DefaultCollisionsWidget::showSections(QHeaderView* header, const QList<int>& logicalIndexes)
544 {
545  if (logicalIndexes.size() < 2)
546  return;
547  int prev = 0;
548  for (int next = 1, end = logicalIndexes.size(); next != end; prev = next, ++next)
549  {
550  for (int index = logicalIndexes[prev], index_end = logicalIndexes[next]; index <= index_end; ++index)
551  header->setSectionHidden(index, false);
552  }
553 }

562 bool DefaultCollisionsWidget::eventFilter(QObject* object, QEvent* event)
563 {
564  if (object != collision_table_)
565  return false; // leave event unhandled
566 
567  if (event->type() == QEvent::Enter)
568  {
569  // grab focus as soon as mouse enters to allow for <space> to work in all cases
570  collision_table_->setFocus();
571  return false;
572  }
573  else if (event->type() == QEvent::KeyPress)
574  {
575  QKeyEvent* key_event = static_cast<QKeyEvent*>(event);
576  if (key_event->key() != Qt::Key_Space)
577  return false;
578 
579  toggleSelection(selection_model_->selection());
580  return true; // no need for further processing
581  }
582 
583  return false;
584 }
585 
586 void DefaultCollisionsWidget::toggleSelection(QItemSelection selection)
587 {
588  // remove hidden rows / columns from selection
589  int rows = model_->rowCount();
590  int cols = model_->columnCount();
591  for (int r = 0; r != rows; ++r)
592  {
593  if (collision_table_->isRowHidden(r))
594  selection.merge(QItemSelection(model_->index(r, 0), model_->index(r, cols - 1)), QItemSelectionModel::Deselect);
595  }
596  for (int c = 0; c != cols; ++c)
597  {
598  if (collision_table_->isColumnHidden(c))
599  selection.merge(QItemSelection(model_->index(0, c), model_->index(rows - 1, c)), QItemSelectionModel::Deselect);
600  }
601 
602  // set all selected items to inverse value of current item
603  const QModelIndex& cur_idx = selection_model_->currentIndex();
604  if (view_mode_buttons_->checkedId() == MATRIX_MODE)
605  {
606  QModelIndex input_index;
607  if (cur_idx.flags() & Qt::ItemIsUserCheckable)
608  input_index = cur_idx; // if current index is checkable, this serves as input
609  else
610  { // search for first checkable index in selection that can serve as input
611  for (const auto idx : selection.indexes())
612  {
613  if (idx.flags() & Qt::ItemIsUserCheckable)
614  {
615  input_index = idx;
616  break;
617  }
618  }
619  if (!input_index.isValid())
620  return; // no valid selection
621  }
622 
623  bool current = model_->data(input_index, Qt::CheckStateRole) == Qt::Checked;
624  CollisionMatrixModel* m = static_cast<CollisionMatrixModel*>(model_);
625  m->setEnabled(selection, !current);
626  }
627  else
628  {
629  bool current = model_->data(model_->index(cur_idx.row(), 2), Qt::CheckStateRole) == Qt::Checked;
630  SortFilterProxyModel* m = static_cast<SortFilterProxyModel*>(model_);
631  m->setEnabled(selection, !current);
632  }
633 }

643 // ******************************************************************************************

647 {

674 // Output Link Pairs to SRDF Format and update the collision matrix
675 // ******************************************************************************************
676 void DefaultCollisionsWidget::linkPairsToSRDF()
677 {
678  // reset the data in the SRDF Writer class
679  config_data_->srdf_->disabled_collisions_.clear();
680 
681  // Create temp disabled collision
682  srdf::Model::DisabledCollision dc;
683 
684  // copy the data in this class's LinkPairMap datastructure to srdf::Model::DisabledCollision format
685  for (moveit_setup_assistant::LinkPairMap::const_iterator pair_it = link_pairs_.begin(); pair_it != link_pairs_.end();
686  ++pair_it)
687  {
688  // Only copy those that are actually disabled
689  if (pair_it->second.disable_check)
690  {
691  dc.link1_ = pair_it->first.first;
692  dc.link2_ = pair_it->first.second;
693  dc.reason_ = moveit_setup_assistant::disabledReasonToString(pair_it->second.reason);
694  config_data_->srdf_->disabled_collisions_.push_back(dc);
695  }
696  }
697 
698  // Update collision_matrix for robot pose's use
699  config_data_->loadAllowedCollisionMatrix();
700 }
701 
702 // ******************************************************************************************
703 // Load Link Pairs from SRDF Format
704 // ******************************************************************************************
705 void DefaultCollisionsWidget::linkPairsFromSRDF()
706 {
707  // Clear all the previous data in the compute_default_collisions tool
708  link_pairs_.clear();
709 
710  // Create new instance of planning scene using pointer
711  planning_scene::PlanningScenePtr scene = config_data_->getPlanningScene()->diff();
712 
713  // Populate link_pairs_ list with every possible n choose 2 combination of links
714  moveit_setup_assistant::computeLinkPairs(*scene, link_pairs_);
715 
716  // Create temp link pair data struct
717  moveit_setup_assistant::LinkPairData link_pair_data;
718  std::pair<std::string, std::string> link_pair;
719 
720  // Loop through all disabled collisions in SRDF and update the comprehensive list that has already been created
721  for (const auto& disabled_collision : config_data_->srdf_->disabled_collisions_)
722  {
723  // Set the link names
724  link_pair.first = disabled_collision.link1_;
725  link_pair.second = disabled_collision.link2_;
726  if (link_pair.first >= link_pair.second)
727  std::swap(link_pair.first, link_pair.second);
728 
729  // Set the link meta data
730  link_pair_data.reason = moveit_setup_assistant::disabledReasonFromString(disabled_collision.reason_);
731  link_pair_data.disable_check = true; // disable checking the collision btw the 2 links
732 
733  // Insert into map
734  link_pairs_[link_pair] = link_pair_data;
735  }
736 }

738 // ******************************************************************************************
739 // Preview whatever element is selected
740 // ******************************************************************************************
741 void DefaultCollisionsWidget::previewSelectedMatrix(const QModelIndex& index)
742 {
743  // Unhighlight all links
744  Q_EMIT unhighlightAll();
745 
746  if (!index.isValid())
747  return;
748 
749  // normalize index
750  int r = index.row();
751  int c = index.column();
752  if (r == c)
753  return;
754  if (r > c)
755  std::swap(r, c);
756 
757  // Highlight link pair
758  const QString& first_link = model_->headerData(r, Qt::Vertical, Qt::DisplayRole).toString();
759  const QString& second_link = model_->headerData(c, Qt::Horizontal, Qt::DisplayRole).toString();
760  uint check_state = model_->data(index, Qt::CheckStateRole).toUInt();
761 
762  QColor color = (check_state == Qt::Checked) ? QColor(0, 255, 0) : QColor(255, 0, 0);
763  Q_EMIT highlightLink(first_link.toStdString(), color);
764  Q_EMIT highlightLink(second_link.toStdString(), color);
765 }

801 bool DefaultCollisionsWidget::focusLost()
802 {
803  if (worker_)
804  {
805  if (QMessageBox::No == QMessageBox::question(this, "Collision Matrix Generation",
806  "Collision Matrix Generation is still active. Cancel computation?",
807  QMessageBox::Yes | QMessageBox::No, QMessageBox::No))
808  return false;
809  worker_->cancel();
810  worker_->wait();
811  }
812 
813  // Copy changes to srdf_writer object and config_data_->allowed_collision_matrix_
814  linkPairsToSRDF();
815  return true;
816 }

818 moveit_setup_assistant::MonitorThread::MonitorThread(const boost::function<void(unsigned int*)>& f,
819  QProgressBar* progress_bar)
820  : progress_(0), canceled_(false)
821 {
822  // start worker thread
823  worker_ = boost::thread(boost::bind(f, &progress_));
824  // connect progress bar for updates
825  if (progress_bar)
826  connect(this, SIGNAL(progress(int)), progress_bar, SLOT(setValue(int)));
827 }
828 
829 void moveit_setup_assistant::MonitorThread::run()
830 {
831  // loop until worker thread is finished or cancel is requested
832  while (!canceled_ && progress_ < 100)
833  {
834  Q_EMIT progress(progress_);
835  QThread::msleep(100); // sleep 100ms
836  }
837 
838  // cancel worker thread
839  if (canceled_)
840  worker_.interrupt();
841 
842  worker_.join();
843 
844  progress_ = 100;
845  Q_EMIT progress(progress_);
846 }
